# Quel fichier contient les clés RSA des machines autorisées à se connecter via SSH ?

# RSA (Rivest–Shamir–Adleman) is one of the first public-key cryptosystems and
# is widely used for secure data transmission. In such a cryptosystem,
# the encryption key is public and it is different from the decryption key
# which is kept secret (private)

# DEDUCTION :
# ls -al ~/.ssh -> Lists the files in your .ssh directory, if they exist
# -> you can see a authorized_keys files
# The file is called authorized_keys, it is located on .ssh folder which is different for each Users.
# ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
